    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Boil a full kettle, then chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>pork</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork loin is cooked, transfer to a plate and set aside</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped shallot </strong>and cook for 2 min</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, then add 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water </strong>and your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then add any <strong>resting juices</strong> from the plate with the steak and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>peppercorn sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sauce is thickening, trim, then add your <strong>green beans</strong> to a separate pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>green beans</strong> and return them to the pot</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the<strong> </strong>drained potatoes</p><p>Crush the potatoes lightly with a masher or the back of a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't press too hard, you only want to crush them!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-loin-with-crushed-potatoes-and-peppercorn-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork loin steak</strong> over the <strong>peppercorn sauce</strong> with the <strong>crushed potatoes</strong> and <strong>green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
